{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, they can get stuck in local minima, which can be problematic when dealing with highdimensional data.",
    "Finally, the curse of dimensionality can make it difficult to determine the optimal clustering of high-dimensional data [64].",
    "(F) Labeling and named entity recognitionWe now move on to the task of labeling the clusters.",
    "To achieve this, we are adopting the method outlined by Liu et al. [65].",
    "Essentially, we label each cluster automatically by identifying the most frequently occurring action-object pair in the phrases contained within the cluster."
  ]
}